HEADWORD: Eosphorite
<hw>E*os"pho*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Gr. <?/
Bringer of morn.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A hydrous phosphate of
alumina and manganese. It is generally of a rose-pink color, -- whence
the name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

